# Goud Chain Environment Variables

# ======================
# NODE CONFIGURATION
# ======================
# NODE_ID=node1
# HTTP_PORT=8080
# P2P_PORT=9000
# PEERS=node2:9000,node3:9000

# ======================
# JWT/SESSION SECRETS
# ======================
# JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_here           # Signs JWT session tokens (auto-generated if not set)
# SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret_here   # Encrypts API keys in JWT tokens (auto-generated if not set)
#
# NOTE: If not provided, secrets are auto-generated on first run and stored in /data directory.
#       For production, set these via environment variables or GitHub Secrets.
#       See docs/SECRET_MANAGEMENT.md for rotation procedures.

# ======================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ======================
# 1. NEVER commit real secrets to git
# 2. Use environment-specific .env files (.env.local, .env.production)
# 3. In production, use secrets management (GitHub Secrets, Kubernetes secrets, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
# 4. Rotate JWT/SESSION secrets every 90 days (see scripts/rotate-secrets.sh)
# 5. User data is encrypted with per-user API keys (not affected by JWT/SESSION secret rotation)
